companyProfile.companyDescription: HDFC Bank Limited (the Bank) is a private bank. The Bank, together with its subsidiaries, is engaged in providing a range of banking and financial services, including retail banking, wholesale banking, treasury operations, insurance, asset management, stockbroking and other financial services businesses. Its segment includes treasury, retail banking, wholesale banking, and other banking operations. The treasury segment consists of net interest earnings from the Bank’s investment portfolio, money market borrowing and lending, and gains or losses on investment operations. The retail banking segment consists of digital banking and other retail banking. The wholesale banking segment provides loans, non-fund facilities and transaction services to corporates, emerging corporates, public sector units, government bodies, and others. The other banking operations segment includes parabanking activities such as credit cards, debit cards, third-party product distribution, and others.

recentNews.headline: Personal loans: Latest interest rates charged by top banks in July 2025
recentNews.intro: Being unsecured, personal loans tend to carry a high rate of interest. Here we list out the interest rates charged by different banks including HDFC, ICICI and Kotak Mahindra
recentNews.imagecaption: Typically, personal loans follow a fixed rate of interest which means the rate stays constant during the tenure of loan

recentNews.headline: Customers want returns. PSBs are waiving the minimum balance levy.
recentNews.intro: PSBs are making a last-ditch attempt to retain customer deposits by dropping penalties for not maintaining a minimum balance in savings accounts.
recentNews.imagecaption: The whole banking industry, not just state-run banks, has been struggling to get people to park their savings with them.

recentNews.headline: Ahead of HBFC Bank bonus issue, this fund manager reveals why he?s bought 10 bank shares monthly for over 15 years
recentNews.intro: HDFC Bank shares: Gurmeet Chadha, CIO & Managing Partner at Complete Circle Wealth, in a recent post on the social media platform X, said that he has been consistently buying 10 shares of HDFC Bank every month for more than 15 years, regardless of Indian stock market conditions.
recentNews.imagecaption: Ahead of HBFC Bank bonus issue, this fund manager reveals why he?s bought 10 bank shares monthly for 15+ years

recentNews.headline: HDB Financial share price plunges nearly 4% to fresh low as Q1 results disappoint
recentNews.intro: HDB Financial share price: The shares of recently-listed HDB Financial declined nearly 4% in intraday trade on Wednesday, July 16, to a new low as investors were disappointed by the dip in the company's profit for the quarter ended June 30 and an increase in provisions.
recentNews.imagecaption: HDB Financial share price plunges nearly 4% to fresh low as Q1 results disappoint

recentNews.headline: Stock Picks: Sagar Doshi suggests Voltas, Samvardhana Motherson, JK Tyre shares to buy today - 16 July
recentNews.intro: India's stock indices opened slightly down, influenced by inflation data and cautious investor sentiment. The Sensex and Nifty 50 declined, while Sagar Doshi predicts Nifty 50 will trade rangebound. He recommends Voltas, Samvardhana Motherson, and JK Tyre as stocks to buy.
recentNews.imagecaption: Stock Picks: Sagar Doshi suggests Voltas, Samvardhana Motherson, JK Tyre shares to buy today - 16 July

recentNews.headline: HDFC Bank Q1 results: Check the date when bank will consider bonus issue, special dividend
